        {
          "nativeId": "alertdialog",
          "name": "Alert and Message Dialogs",
          "aliases": [],
          "summary": {
            "text": "An alert dialog is a modal dialog that interrupts the user's workflow to communicate an important message and acquire a response. Examples include action confirmation prompts and error message confirmations. The alertdialog role enables assistive technologies and browsers to distinguish alert dialogs from other dialogs so they have the option of giving alert dialogs special treatment, such as playing a system alert sound.",
            "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/alertdialog/#about"
          },
          "kind": "pattern",
          "canonicalUrl": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/alertdialog/",
          "sections": [
            {
              "nativeId": "about",
              "title": "About This Pattern",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/alertdialog/#about",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "examples",
              "title": "Example",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/alertdialog/#examples",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "keyboard_interaction",
              "title": "Keyboard Interaction",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/alertdialog/#keyboard_interaction",
              "content": "See the keyboard interaction section for the modal dialog pattern ."
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "roles_states_properties",
              "title": "WAI-ARIA Roles, States, and Properties",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/alertdialog/#roles_states_properties",
              "content": "• The element that contains all elements of the dialog, including the alert message and any dialog buttons, has role alertdialog .\n• The dialog container element has aria-modal set to true .\n• The element with role alertdialog has either:\n• A value for aria-labelledby that refers to the element containing the title of the dialog if the dialog has a visible label.\n• A value for aria-label if the dialog does not have a visible label.\n• The element with role alertdialog has a value set for aria-describedby that refers to the element containing the alert message.\nNote\n• Because marking a dialog modal by setting aria-modal to true can prevent users of some assistive technologies from perceiving content outside the dialog, users of those technologies will experience severe negative ramifications if a dialog is marked modal but does not behave as a modal for other users.\nSo, mark a dialog modal only when both:\n• Application code prevents all users from interacting in any way with content outside of it.\n• Visual styling obscures the content outside of it.\n• The aria-modal property introduced by ARIA 1.1 replaces aria-hidden for informing assistive technologies that content outside a dialog is inert.\nHowever, in legacy dialog implementations where aria-hidden is used to make content outside a dialog inert for assistive technology users, it is important that:\n• aria-hidden is set to true on each element containing a portion of the inert layer.\n• The dialog element is not a descendant of any element that has aria-hidden set to true ."
            }
          ],
          "links": [
            {
