        {
          "nativeId": "meter",
          "name": "Meter",
          "aliases": [],
          "summary": {
            "text": "A meter is a graphical display of a numeric value that varies within a defined range. For example, a meter could be used to depict a device's current battery percentage or a car's fuel level.",
            "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/meter/#about"
          },
          "kind": "pattern",
          "canonicalUrl": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/meter/",
          "sections": [
            {
              "nativeId": "about",
              "title": "About This Pattern",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/meter/#about",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "examples",
              "title": "Example",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/meter/#examples",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "keyboard_interaction",
              "title": "Keyboard Interaction",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/meter/#keyboard_interaction",
              "content": "Not applicable."
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "roles_states_properties",
              "title": "WAI-ARIA Roles, States, and Properties",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/meter/#roles_states_properties",
              "content": "• The element serving as the meter has a role of meter .\n• The meter has aria-valuenow set to a decimal value between aria-valuemin and aria-valuemax representing the current value of the meter.\n• The meter has aria-valuemin set to a decimal value less than aria-valuemax .\n• The meter has aria-valuemax set to a decimal value greater than aria-valuemin .\n• Assistive technologies often present aria-valuenow as a percentage.\nIf conveying the value of the meter only in terms of a percentage would not be user friendly, the aria-valuetext property is set to a string that makes the meter value understandable.\nFor example, a battery meter value might be conveyed as aria-valuetext=\"50% (6 hours) remaining\" .\n• If the meter has a visible label, it is referenced by aria-labelledby on the element with role meter .\nOtherwise, the element with role meter has a label provided by aria-label ."
            }
          ],
          "links": [
            {
              "kind": "docs",
