        {
          "nativeId": "radio",
          "name": "Radio Group",
          "aliases": [],
          "summary": {
            "text": "A radio group is a set of checkable buttons, known as radio buttons, where no more than one of the buttons can be checked at a time. Some implementations may initialize the set with all buttons in the unchecked state in order to force the user to check one of the buttons before moving past a certain point in the workflow.",
            "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/radio/#about"
          },
          "kind": "pattern",
          "canonicalUrl": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/radio/",
          "sections": [
            {
              "nativeId": "about",
              "title": "About This Pattern",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/radio/#about",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "examples",
              "title": "Examples",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/radio/#examples",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "keyboard_interaction",
              "title": "Keyboard Interaction",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/radio/#keyboard_interaction",
              "content": "For Radio Groups Not Contained in a Toolbar\nThis section describes the keyboard interaction implemented for most radio groups.\nFor the special case of a radio group nested inside a toolbar , use the keyboard interaction described in the following section.\n• Tab and Shift + Tab : Move focus into and out of the radio group.\nWhen focus moves into a radio group:\n• If a radio button is checked, focus is set on the checked button.\n• If none of the radio buttons are checked, focus is set on the first radio button in the group.\n• Space : checks the focused radio button if it is not already checked.\n• Right Arrow and Down Arrow : move focus to the next radio button in the group, uncheck the previously focused button, and check the newly focused button.\nIf focus is on the last button, focus moves to the first button.\n• Left Arrow and Up Arrow : move focus to the previous radio button in the group, uncheck the previously focused button, and check the newly focused button.\nIf focus is on the first button, focus moves to the last button.\nNote\nThe initial focus behavior described above differs slightly from the behavior provided by some browsers for native HTML radio groups.\nIn some browsers, if none of the radio buttons are selected, moving focus into the radio group with Shift + Tab will place focus on the last radio button instead of the first radio button."
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "roles_states_properties",
              "title": "WAI-ARIA Roles, States, and Properties",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/radio/#roles_states_properties",
              "content": "• The radio buttons are contained in or owned by an element with role radiogroup .\n• Each radio button element has role radio .\n• If a radio button is checked, the radio element has aria-checked set to true .\nIf it is not checked, it has aria-checked set to false .\n• Each radio element is labelled by its content, has a visible label referenced by aria-labelledby , or has a label specified with aria-label .\n• The radiogroup element has a visible label referenced by aria-labelledby or has a label specified with aria-label .\n• If elements providing additional information about either the radio group or each radio button are present, those elements are referenced by the radiogroup element or radio elements with the aria-describedby property."
            }
          ],
          "links": [
