        {
          "nativeId": "slider",
          "name": "Slider",
          "aliases": [],
          "summary": {
            "text": "A slider is an input where the user selects a value from within a given range. Sliders typically have a slider thumb that can be moved along a bar, rail, or track to change the value of the slider.",
            "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/slider/#about"
          },
          "kind": "pattern",
          "canonicalUrl": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/slider/",
          "sections": [
            {
              "nativeId": "about",
              "title": "About This Pattern",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/slider/#about",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "examples",
              "title": "Examples",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/slider/#examples",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "keyboard_interaction",
              "title": "Keyboard Interaction",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/slider/#keyboard_interaction",
              "content": "• Right Arrow : Increase the value of the slider by one step.\n• Up Arrow : Increase the value of the slider by one step.\n• Left Arrow : Decrease the value of the slider by one step.\n• Down Arrow : Decrease the value of the slider by one step.\n• Home : Set the slider to the first allowed value in its range.\n• End : Set the slider to the last allowed value in its range.\n• Page Up (Optional): Increase the slider value by an amount larger than the step change made by Up Arrow .\n• Page Down (Optional): Decrease the slider value by an amount larger than the step change made by Down Arrow .\nNote\n• Focus is placed on the slider (the visual object that the mouse user would move, also known as the thumb.\n• In some circumstances, reversing the direction of the value change for the keys specified above, e.g., having Up Arrow decrease the value, could create a more intuitive experience."
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "roles_states_properties",
              "title": "WAI-ARIA Roles, States, and Properties",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/slider/#roles_states_properties",
              "content": "• The element serving as the focusable slider control has role slider .\n• The slider element has the aria-valuenow property set to a decimal value representing the current value of the slider.\n• The slider element has the aria-valuemin property set to a decimal value representing the minimum allowed value of the slider.\n• The slider element has the aria-valuemax property set to a decimal value representing the maximum allowed value of the slider.\n• If the value of aria-valuenow is not user-friendly, e.g., the day of the week is represented by a number, the aria-valuetext property is set to a string that makes the slider value understandable, e.g., \"Monday\".\n• If the slider has a visible label, it is referenced by aria-labelledby on the slider element.\nOtherwise, the slider element has a label provided by aria-label .\n• If the slider is vertically oriented, it has aria-orientation set to vertical .\nThe default value of aria-orientation for a slider is horizontal ."
            }
          ],
          "links": [
            {
              "kind": "docs",
              "label": null,
