        {
          "nativeId": "switch",
          "name": "Switch",
          "aliases": [],
          "summary": {
            "text": "A switch is an input widget that allows users to choose one of two values: on or off . Switches are similar to checkboxes and toggle buttons , which can also serve as binary inputs. One difference, however, is that switches can only be used for binary input while checkboxes and toggle buttons allow implementations the option of supporting a third middle state. Checkboxes can be checked or not checked and can optionally also allow for a partially checked state. Toggle buttons can be pressed or not pressed and can optionally allow for a partially pressed state.",
            "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/#about"
          },
          "kind": "pattern",
          "canonicalUrl": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/",
          "sections": [
            {
              "nativeId": "about",
              "title": "About This Pattern",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/#about",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "examples",
              "title": "Examples",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/#examples",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "keyboard_interaction",
              "title": "Keyboard Interaction",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/#keyboard_interaction",
              "content": "• Space : When focus is on the switch, changes the state of the switch.\n• Enter (Optional): When focus is on the switch, changes the state of the switch."
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "roles_states_properties",
              "title": "WAI-ARIA Roles, States, and Properties",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/#roles_states_properties",
              "content": "• The switch has role switch .\n• The switch has an accessible label provided by one of the following:\n• Visible text content contained within the element with role switch .\n• A visible label referenced by the value of aria-labelledby set on the element with role switch .\n• aria-label set on the element with role switch .\n• When on , the switch element has state aria-checked set to true .\n• When off , the switch element has state aria-checked set to false .\n• If the switch element is an HTML input[type=\"checkbox\"] , it uses the HTML checked attribute instead of the aria-checked property.\n• If a set of switches is presented as a logical group with a visible label, either:\n• The switches are included in an element with role group that has the property aria-labelledby set to the ID of the element containing the group label.\n• The set is contained in an HTML fieldset and the label for the set is contained in an HTML legend element.\n• If the presentation includes additional descriptive static text relevant to a switch or switch group, the switch or switch group has the property aria-describedby set to the ID of the element containing the description."
            }
          ],
          "links": [
            {
              "kind": "docs",
              "label": null,
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/switch/"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "label": null,
