        {
          "nativeId": "tabs",
          "name": "Tabs",
          "aliases": [],
          "summary": {
            "text": "Tabs are a set of layered sections of content, known as tab panels, that display one panel of content at a time. Each tab panel has an associated tab element, that when activated, displays the panel. The list of tab elements is arranged along one edge of the currently displayed panel, most commonly the top edge.",
            "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/#about"
          },
          "kind": "pattern",
          "canonicalUrl": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/",
          "sections": [
            {
              "nativeId": "about",
              "title": "About This Pattern",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/#about",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "examples",
              "title": "Examples",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/#examples",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "keyboard_interaction",
              "title": "Keyboard Interaction",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/#keyboard_interaction",
              "content": "For the tab list:\n• Tab :\n• When focus moves into the tab list, places focus on the active tab element.\n• When the tab list contains the focus, moves focus to the next element in the page tab sequence outside the tablist, which is the tabpanel unless the first element containing meaningful content inside the tabpanel is focusable.\n• When focus is on a tab element in a horizontal tab list:\n• Left Arrow : moves focus to the previous tab.\nIf focus is on the first tab, moves focus to the last tab.\nOptionally, activates the newly focused tab (See note below).\n• Right Arrow : Moves focus to the next tab.\nIf focus is on the last tab element, moves focus to the first tab.\nOptionally, activates the newly focused tab (See note below).\n• When focus is on a tab in a tablist with either horizontal or vertical orientation:\n• Space or Enter : Activates the tab if it was not activated automatically on focus.\n• Home (Optional): Moves focus to the first tab.\nOptionally, activates the newly focused tab (See note below).\n• End (Optional): Moves focus to the last tab.\nOptionally, activates the newly focused tab (See note below).\n• Shift + F10 : If the tab has an associated popup menu, opens the menu.\n• Delete (Optional): If deletion is allowed, deletes (closes) the current tab element and its associated tab panel, sets focus on the tab following the tab that was closed, and optionally activates the newly focused tab.\nIf there is not a tab that followed the tab that was deleted, e.g., the deleted tab was the right-most tab in a left-to-right horizontal tab list, sets focus on and optionally activates the tab that preceded the deleted tab.\nIf the application allows all tabs to be deleted, and the user deletes the last remaining tab in the tab list, the application moves focus to another element that provides a logical work flow.\nAs an alternative to Delete , or in addition to supporting Delete , the delete function is available in a context menu.\nNote\n• It is recommended that tabs activate automatically when they receive focus as long as their associated tab panels are displayed without noticeable latency.\nThis typically requires tab panel content to be preloaded.\nOtherwise, automatic activation slows focus movement, which significantly hampers users' ability to navigate efficiently across the tab list.\nFor additional guidance, see Deciding When to Make Selection Automatically Follow Focus .\n• When a tab list has its aria-orientation set to vertical :\n• Down Arrow performs as Right Arrow is described above.\n• Up Arrow performs as Left Arrow is described above.\n• If the tab list is horizontal, it does not listen for Down Arrow or Up Arrow so those keys can provide their normal browser scrolling functions even when focus is inside the tab list.\n• When the tabpanel does not contain any focusable elements or the first element with content is not focusable, the tabpanel should set tabindex=\"0\" to include it in the tab sequence of the page."
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "roles_states_properties",
              "title": "WAI-ARIA Roles, States, and Properties",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/#roles_states_properties",
              "content": "• The element that serves as the container for the set of tabs has role tablist .\n• Each element that serves as a tab has role tab and is contained within the element with role tablist .\n• Each element that contains the content panel for a tab has role tabpanel .\n• If the tab list has a visible label, the element with role tablist has aria-labelledby set to a value that refers to the labelling element.\nOtherwise, the tablist element has a label provided by aria-label .\n• Each element with role tab has the property aria-controls referring to its associated tabpanel element.\n• The active tab element has the state aria-selected set to true and all other tab elements have it set to false .\n• Each element with role tabpanel has the property aria-labelledby referring to its associated tab element.\n• If a tab element has a popup menu, it has the property aria-haspopup set to either menu or true .\n• If the tablist element is vertically oriented, it has the property aria-orientation set to vertical .\nThe default value of aria-orientation for a tablist element is horizontal ."
            }
          ],
          "links": [
            {
              "kind": "docs",
              "label": null,
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "label": null,
              "url": "https://github.com/w3c/aria-practices/blob/18c1a2fca626f7aeb33270e23ae9b18833e2164d/content/patterns/tabs/tabs-pattern.html"
            }
          ],
          "examples": [
            {
              "nativeId": "tabs-automatic",
              "title": "Tabs With Automatic Activation",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/examples/tabs-automatic.html"
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "tabs-manual",
              "title": "Tabs With Manual Activation",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/examples/tabs-manual.html"
            }
          ],
          "relationships": [],
          "provenance": {
            "providerId": "aria-apg",
            "repository": "https://github.com/w3c/aria-practices",
            "revision": "18c1a2fca626f7aeb33270e23ae9b18833e2164d",
            "sourcePath": "content/patterns/tabs/tabs-pattern.html"
          }
        },
        {
          "nativeId": "toolbar",
          "name": "Toolbar",
          "aliases": [],
          "summary": {
            "text": "A toolbar is a container for grouping a set of controls, such as buttons, menubuttons, or checkboxes.",
            "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/toolbar/#about"
          },
          "kind": "pattern",
          "canonicalUrl": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/toolbar/",
          "sections": [
            {
              "nativeId": "about",
              "title": "About This Pattern",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/toolbar/#about",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "examples",
              "title": "Example",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/toolbar/#examples",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "keyboard_interaction",
              "title": "Keyboard Interaction",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/toolbar/#keyboard_interaction",
              "content": "• Tab and Shift + Tab : Move focus into and out of the toolbar.\nWhen focus moves into a toolbar:\n• If focus is moving into the toolbar for the first time, focus is set on the first control that is not disabled.\n• If the toolbar has previously contained focus, focus is optionally set on the control that last had focus.\nOtherwise, it is set on the first control that is not disabled.\n• For a horizontal toolbar (the default):\n• Left Arrow : Moves focus to the previous control.\nOptionally, focus movement may wrap from the first element to the last element.\n• Right Arrow : Moves focus to the next control.\nOptionally, focus movement may wrap from the last element to the first element.\n• Home (Optional): Moves focus to first element.\n• End (Optional): Moves focus to last element.\nNote\n• If the items in a toolbar are arranged vertically:\n• Down Arrow performs as Right Arrow is described above.\n• Up Arrow performs as Left Arrow is described above.\n• Typically, disabled elements are not focusable when navigating with a keyboard.\nHowever, in circumstances where discoverability of a function is crucial, it may be helpful if disabled controls are focusable so screen reader users are more likely to be aware of their presence.\nFor additional guidance, see Focusability of disabled controls .\n• In applications where quick access to a toolbar is important, such as accessing an editor's toolbar from its text area, a documented shortcut key for moving focus from the relevant context to its corresponding toolbar is recommended."
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "roles_states_properties",
              "title": "WAI-ARIA Roles, States, and Properties",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/toolbar/#roles_states_properties",
              "content": "• The element that serves as the toolbar container has role toolbar .\n• If the toolbar has a visible label, it is referenced by aria-labelledby on the toolbar element.\nOtherwise, the toolbar element has a label provided by aria-label .\n• If the controls are arranged vertically, the toolbar element has aria-orientation set to vertical .\nThe default orientation is horizontal."
            }
          ],
          "links": [
            {
              "kind": "docs",
              "label": null,
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/toolbar/"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "label": null,
              "url": "https://github.com/w3c/aria-practices/blob/18c1a2fca626f7aeb33270e23ae9b18833e2164d/content/patterns/toolbar/toolbar-pattern.html"
            }
          ],
          "examples": [
            {
              "nativeId": "toolbar",
              "title": "Toolbar Example",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/toolbar/examples/toolbar.html"
            }
          ],
          "relationships": [],
          "provenance": {
            "providerId": "aria-apg",
