          "nativeId": "windowsplitter",
          "name": "Window Splitter",
          "aliases": [],
          "summary": {
            "text": "NOTE: ARIA 1.1 introduced changes to the separator role so it behaves as a widget when focusable. While this pattern has been revised to match the ARIA 1.1 specification, the task force will not complete its review until a functional example that matches the ARIA 1.1 specification is complete. Progress on this pattern is tracked by issue 129.",
            "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/windowsplitter/#about"
          },
          "kind": "pattern",
          "canonicalUrl": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/windowsplitter/",
          "sections": [
            {
              "nativeId": "about",
              "title": "About This Pattern",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/windowsplitter/#about",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "example",
              "title": "Example",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/windowsplitter/#example",
              "content": null
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "keyboard_interaction",
              "title": "Keyboard Interaction",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/windowsplitter/#keyboard_interaction",
              "content": "• Left Arrow : Moves a vertical splitter to the left.\n• Right Arrow : Moves a vertical splitter to the right.\n• Up Arrow : Moves a horizontal splitter up.\n• Down Arrow : Moves a horizontal splitter down.\n• Enter : If the primary pane is not collapsed, collapses the pane.\nIf the pane is collapsed, restores the splitter to its previous position.\n• Home (Optional): Moves splitter to the position that gives the primary pane its smallest allowed size.\nThis may completely collapse the primary pane.\n• End (Optional): Moves splitter to the position that gives the primary pane its largest allowed size.\nThis may completely collapse the secondary pane.\n• F6 (Optional): Cycle through window panes.\nNote\nA fixed size splitter omits implementation of the arrow keys."
            },
            {
              "nativeId": "roles_states_properties",
              "title": "WAI-ARIA Roles, States, and Properties",
              "url": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/windowsplitter/#roles_states_properties",
              "content": "• The element that serves as the focusable splitter has role separator .\n• The separator element has the aria-valuenow property set to a decimal value representing the current position of the separator.\n• The separator element has the aria-valuemin property set to a decimal value that represents the position where the primary pane has its minimum size.\nThis is typically 0 .\n• The separator element has the aria-valuemax property set to a decimal value that represents the position where the primary pane has its maximum size.\nThis is typically 100 .\n• If the primary pane has a visible label, it is referenced by aria-labelledby on the separator element.\nOtherwise, the separator element has a label provided by aria-label .\n• The separator element has aria-controls referring to the primary pane."
            }
          ],
          "links": [
